isiana}}\nThis is a list of people who have served as mayor of the city of [[Shreveport, Louisiana]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Mayor !! From !! To !! Party !! Notes\n|-{{Party shading/Independent}}\n| [[Angus McNeill]] || 1836 || 1839 || None || President of Shreve Town Co.\n|-{{Party shading/Whig}}\n| [[John Octavius Sewall]] || 1839 || 1840 || [[Whig Party (United States)|Whig]] || First Elected Mayor\n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[William Walton George]], M.D. || 1840 || 1840 || [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] || \n|-{{Party shading/Independent}}\n| [[Samuel W. Briggs]] || 1841 || 1841 || None ||\n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[William Walton George]], M.D. || 1842 || 1843 || [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] || \n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[John N. Howell]] || 1844 || 1844 || [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] || \n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[Joseph Clinton Beall]] || 1845 || 1845 || [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] || \n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[Lawrence Pike Crain]] || 1846 || 1847 || [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] || \n|-{{Party shading/Whig}}\n| [[Robert Nathaniel Wood]] || 1847 || 1847 || [[Whig Party (United States)|Whig]]/[[Know Nothing]] || Died in Mexico\n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[John Morgan Landrum]] || 1848 || 1848 || [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] || Elected to Congress\n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| Rev. [[John Bryce]] || 1849 || 1849 || [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] || \n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[Robert W. Cooke]] || 1850 || 1850 || [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] || \n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[Joseph Clinton Beall]] || 1851 || 1853 || [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] || \n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[John Wallace Jones]] || 1854 || 1857 || [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] || \n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n| [[