{"title_page": "Pituicytoma", "text_new": "{{Infobox medical condition (new)\n| name            = Pituicytoma\n| synonyms        = \n| image           = Pituicytoma.jpg\n| caption         = Biopsy specimen of a pituicytoma of the posterior pituitary gland ([[H&E stain]], x200 magnification)\n| pronounce       = \n| field           = \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\n'''Pituicytoma''' is a rare [[brain tumor]]. It grows at the base of the brain from the [[pituitary gland]]. This tumor is thought to be derived from the [[parenchymal cells]] of the [[posterior lobe]] of the pituitary gland, called [[pituicytes]]. Some researchers<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Cenacchi|first=G.|last2=Giovenali|first2=P.|last3=Castrioto|first3=C.|last4=Giangaspero|first4=F.|date=July 2001|title=Pituicytoma: ultrastructural evidence of a possible origin from folliculo-stellate cells of the adenohypophysis|journal=Ultrastructural Pathology|volume=25|issue=4|pages=309\u2013312|issn=0191-3123|pmid=11577776|doi=10.1080/019131201753136331}}</ref> believe that they arise from the [[folliculostellate cell]]s in the [[anterior lobe]] of the pituitary. As such, it is a low-grade [[glioma]]. It occurs in adults and symptoms include [[visual disturbance]] and [[endocrine dysfunction]]. They are often mistaken for [[pituitary adenoma]]s which have a similar presentation and occur in the same location. The treatment consists of surgical resection, which is curative in most cases.<ref name=\"Feng\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Feng M, Carmichael JD, Bonert V, Bannykh S, Mamelak AN |title= Surgical management of pituicytomas: case series and comprehensive literature review. |journal= Pituitary |volume=17 | issue = 5  |year=2014 |pages= 399\u2013413|pmid= 24037647 |doi=10.1007/s11102-013-0515-z }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Brat D, Scheithauer B, Staugaitis S, Holtzman N, Morgello S, Burger P | title = Pituicytoma: A distinctive low grade glioma of the neurohypophysis | url = | journal = Am J Surg Pathol | volume = 24 | pages = 362\u2013368| year = 2000 | doi=10.1097/00000478-200003000-00004}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Cenacchi G, Giovenali P, Castrioto C, Giangaspero F | title = Pituicytoma: Ultrastructural evidence of a possible origin from folliculo-stellate cells of the adenohypophysis | url = | journal = Ultrastruct Pathol | volume = 25 | issue = 4 | pages = 309\u2013312| year = 2001 | doi=10.1080/019131201753136331 | pmid = 11577776}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Secci F, Merciadri P, Criminelli Rossi D, D'Andrea A, Zona G | title = Pituicytomas: radiological findings, clinical behaviour and surgical management | url = | journal = Acta Neurochirurgica | volume = 154 | issue = 4 | pages = 649\u2013657| year = 2012 | doi=10.1007/s00701-011-1235-7}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Danila DC, Zhang X, Zhou Y, Dickerson GR, Fletcher JA, Hedley-Whyte ET, Selig MK, Johnson SR, Klibanski A | title = A human pituitary tumor-derived folliculo-stellate cell line | url = | journal = J Clin Endocrinol Metab | volume = 85 | issue = 3 | pages = 1180\u20131187| year = 2000 | doi=10.1210/jc.85.3.1180}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Figarella-Branger D, Dufour H, Fernandez C, Bouvier-Labit C, Grisoli F, Pellissier JF | title = Pituicytomas, a mis-diagnosed benign tumor of the neurohypophysis: Report of three cases | url = | journal = Acta Neuropathol | volume = 104 | pages = 313\u2013319| year = 2002 | doi = 10.1007/s00401-002-0557-1 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Hurley T, D'Angelo C, Clasen R, Wilkinson S, Passavoy R | title = Magnetic resonance imaging and pathological analysis of a pituicytoma: Case report | url = | journal = Neurosurgery | volume = 35 | pages = 314\u2013317| year = 1994 | doi=10.1097/00006123-199408000-00021}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Inoue K, Couch EF, Takano K, Ogawa S | title = The structure and function of folliculo-stellate cells in the anterior pituitary gland | url = | journal = Arch Histol Cytol | volume = 62 | issue = 3 | pages = 205\u2013218| year = 1999 | doi=10.1679/aohc.62.205 | pmid = 10495875}}\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n| DiseasesDB      = \n| ICD10           = {{ICD10|C|75|1}}\n| ICD9            = \n| ICDO            = 9432/1\n| OMIM            = \n| MedlinePlus     = \n| eMedicineSubj   = \n| eMedicineTopic  = \n| MeshID          = \n| Orphanet        = 251623\n| SNOMED CT       = 608817003\n}}\n{{Central nervous system tumors}}\n{{Endocrine gland neoplasia}}\n\n[[Category:Endocrine neoplasia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox medical condition (new)\n| name            = Pituicytoma\n| synonyms        = \n| image           = Pituicytoma.jpg\n| caption         = Biopsy specimen of a pituicytoma of the posterior pituitary gland ([[H&E stain]], x200 magnification)\n| pronounce       = \n| field           = \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\n'''Pituicytoma''' is a rare [[brain tumor]]. It grows at the base of the brain from the [[pituitary gland]]. This tumor is thought to be derived from the [[parenchymal cells]] of the [[posterior lobe]] of the pituitary gland, called [[pituicytes]]. Some researchers<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Cenacchi|first=G.|last2=Giovenali|first2=P.|last3=Castrioto|first3=C.|last4=Giangaspero|first4=F.|date=July 2001|title=Pituicytoma: ultrastructural evidence of a possible origin from folliculo-stellate cells of the adenohypophysis|journal=Ultrastructural Pathology|volume=25|issue=4|pages=309\u2013312|issn=0191-3123|pmid=11577776|doi=10.1080/019131201753136331}}</ref> believe that they arise from the [[folliculostellate cell]]s in the [[anterior lobe]] of the pituitary. As such, it is a low-grade [[glioma]]. It occurs in adults and symptoms include [[visual disturbance]] and [[endocrine dysfunction]]. They are often mistaken for [[pituitary adenoma]]s which have a similar presentation and occur in the same location. The treatment consists of surgical resection, which is curative in most cases.<ref name=\"Feng\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Feng M, Carmichael JD, Bonert V, Bannykh S, Mamelak AN |title= Surgical management of pituicytomas: case series and comprehensive literature review. |journal= Pituitary |volume=17 | issue = 5  |year=2014 |pages= 399\u2013413|pmid= 24037647 |doi=10.1007/s11102-013-0515-z }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Brat D, Scheithauer B, Staugaitis S, Holtzman N, Morgello S, Burger P | title = Pituicytoma: A distinctive low grade glioma of the neurohypophysis | url = | journal = Am J Surg Pathol | volume = 24 | pages = 362\u2013368| year = 2000 | doi=10.1097/00000478-200003000-00004}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Cenacchi G, Giovenali P, Castrioto C, Giangaspero F | title = Pituicytoma: Ultrastructural evidence of a possible origin from folliculo-stellate cells of the adenohypophysis | url = | journal = Ultrastruct Pathol | volume = 25 | issue = 4 | pages = 309\u2013312| year = 2001 | doi=10.1080/019131201753136331 | pmid = 11577776}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Secci F, Merciadri P, Criminelli Rossi D, D'Andrea A, Zona G | title = Pituicytomas: radiological findings, clinical behaviour and surgical management | url = | journal = Acta Neurochirurgica | volume = 154 | issue = 4 | pages = 649\u2013657| year = 2012 | doi=10.1007/s00701-011-1235-7}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Danila DC, Zhang X, Zhou Y, Dickerson GR, Fletcher JA, Hedley-Whyte ET, Selig MK, Johnson SR, Klibanski A | title = A human pituitary tumor-derived folliculo-stellate cell line | url = | journal = J Clin Endocrinol Metab | volume = 85 | issue = 3 | pages = 1180\u20131187| year = 2000 | doi=10.1210/jc.85.3.1180}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Figarella-Branger D, Dufour H, Fernandez C, Bouvier-Labit C, Grisoli F, Pellissier JF | title = Pituicytomas, a mis-diagnosed benign tumor of the neurohypophysis: Report of three cases | url = | journal = Acta Neuropathol | volume = 104 | pages = 313\u2013319| year = 2002 | doi = 10.1007/s00401-002-0557-1 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Hurley T, D'Angelo C, Clasen R, Wilkinson S, Passavoy R | title = Magnetic resonance imaging and pathological analysis of a pituicytoma: Case report | url = | journal = Neurosurgery | volume = 35 | pages = 314\u2013317| year = 1994 | doi=10.1097/00006123-199408000-00021}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Inoue K, Couch EF, Takano K, Ogawa S | title = The structure and function of folliculo-stellate cells in the anterior pituitary gland | url = | journal = Arch Histol Cytol | volume = 62 | issue = 3 | pages = 205\u2013218| year = 1999 | doi=10.1679/aohc.62.205 | pmid = 10495875}}\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n|  DiseasesDB     =  \n|  ICD10          = {{ICD10|C|75|1}} \n|  ICD9           =  \n|  ICDO           = 9432/1 \n|  OMIM           =  \n|  MedlinePlus    =  \n|  eMedicineSubj  =  \n|  eMedicineTopic =  \n|  MeshID         =  \n|  Orphanet       = 251623\n}}\n{{Central nervous system tumors}}\n{{Endocrine gland neoplasia}}\n\n[[Category:Endocrine neoplasia]]\n", "name_user": "Dismanet", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding new medical resources.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pituicytoma"}
