{"title_page": "Eug\u00e8ne Van Roosbroeck", "text_new": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Eug\u00e8ne Van Roosbroeck\n| image          = Eugne-van-Roosbroeck-1432738256.jpg\n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| nickname       = \n| birth_date     = {{Birth date|1928|5|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Noorderwijk]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     = {{Death date and age|df=yes|2018|3|28|1928|5|13}}\n| death_place    = Noorderwijk, Belgium\n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| currentteam    = \n| discipline     = \n| role           = \n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry | {{flag|BEL}} }}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[cycling (sport)|cycling]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold|London 1948|[[Cycling at the 1948 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team road race|Team road race]]}}\n| show-medals = yes\n}}\n\n'''Eug\u00e8ne Van Roosbroeck''' (13 May 1928 \u2013 28 March 2018) was a Belgian [[racing cyclist]] from [[Noorderwijk]] ([[Antwerp (province)|Antwerp province]]). He won a gold medal in [[Cycling at the 1948 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team road race|team road race]] at the [[Cycling at the 1948 Summer Olympics|1948 Summer Olympics]] in [[London]], together with [[Lode Wouters]] and [[Leon De Lathouwer]].<ref name=sref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/va/eugene-van-roosbroeck-1.html |title=Eug\u00e8ne Van Roosbroeck |publisher=Sports-reference.com |accessdate=26 February 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/wielrennen/1.3170223|title=Belgische goudenmedaillewinnaar van Spelen 1948 overleden|language=Dutch|trans-title=Belgian golden medal winner of Games 1948 passed away|date=29 March 2018|accessdate=30 March 2018|work=[[Sporza]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330012511/http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/wielrennen/1.3170223|archive-date=30 March 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAfter that Olympic race, the Belgian cyclists were not aware that there was a team competition, and returned to Belgium, missing the medal ceremony. Many years later, Van Roosbroeck heard that [[Andr\u00e9 Nelis]] was given a copy of his lost medal, and requested the Belgian Olympic Committee to get the medal that he never received, and was given one in 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.demorgen.be/sport/eugeen-van-roosbroeck-krijgt-na-62-jaar-zijn-gouden-medaille-b4a749f1/|title=Eugeen Van Roosbroeck krijgt na 62 jaar zijn gouden medaille|language=Dutch|trans-title=Eugeen Van Roosbroeck gets his golden medal after 62 years|work=[[De Morgen]]|date=4 June 2010|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Footer Olympic Champions Belgium Men}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Van Roosbroeck, Eugene}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:2018 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Antwerp]]\n[[Category:Belgian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1948 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of Belgium]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for Belgium]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in cycling]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1948 Summer Olympics]]\n\n\n{{Belgium-cycling-bio-1920s-stub}}\n{{Belgium-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Eug\u00e8ne Van Roosbroeck\n| image          = Eugne-van-Roosbroeck-1432738256.jpg\n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| nickname       = \n| birth_date     = {{Birth date|1928|5|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Noorderwijk]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     = {{Death date and age|df=yes|2018|3|28|1928|5|13}}\n| death_place    = Noorderwijk, Belgium\n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| currentteam    = \n| discipline     = \n| role           = \n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry | {{flag|BEL}} }}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[cycling (sport)|cycling]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold|London 1948|[[Cycling at the 1948 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team road race|Team road race]]}}\n| show-medals = yes\n}}\n\n'''Eug\u00e8ne Van Roosbroeck''' (13 May 1928 \u2013 28 March 2018) was a Belgian [[racing cyclist]] from [[Noorderwijk]] ([[Antwerp (province)|Antwerp province]]). He won a gold medal in [[Cycling at the 1948 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team road race|team road race]] at the [[Cycling at the 1948 Summer Olympics|1948 Summer Olympics]] in [[London]], together with [[Lode Wouters]] and [[Leon De Lathouwer]].<ref name=sref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/va/eugene-van-roosbroeck-1.html |title=Eug\u00e8ne Van Roosbroeck |publisher=Sports-reference.com |accessdate=26 February 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/wielrennen/1.3170223|title=Belgische goudenmedaillewinnaar van Spelen 1948 overleden|language=Dutch|trans-title=Belgian golden medal winner of Games 1948 passed away|date=29 March 2018|accessdate=30 March 2018|work=[[Sporza]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330012511/http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/wielrennen/1.3170223|archive-date=30 March 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAfter that Olympic race, the Belgian cyclists were not aware that there was a team competition, and returned to Belgium, missing the medal ceremony. Many years later, Van Roosbroeck heard that [[Andr\u00e9 Nelis]] was given a copy of his lost medal, and requested the Belgian Olympic Committee to get the medal that he never received, and was given one in 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.demorgen.be/sport/eugeen-van-roosbroeck-krijgt-na-62-jaar-zijn-gouden-medaille-b4a749f1/|title=Eugeen Van Roosbroeck krijgt na 62 jaar zijn gouden medaille|language=Dutch|trans-title=Eugeen Van Roosbroeck gets his golden medal after 62 years|work=[[De Morgen]]|date=4 June 2010|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Footer Olympic Champions Belgium Men}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Van Roosbroeck, Eugene}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:2018 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Antwerp]]\n[[Category:Belgian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1948 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of Belgium]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for Belgium]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in cycling]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1948 Summer Olympics]]\n\n\n{{Belgium-cycling-bio-1920s-stub}}\n{{Belgium-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lepricavark", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:added short description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eug%C3%A8ne_Van_Roosbroeck"}
